cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the problem of overfitting in training machine learning models, specifically deep neural networks. It also proposes a regularization technique to drop visible and hidden units in a deep neural network using Ising energy of the network. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with deep neural networks and their optimization. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the proposed technique is applied to classification tasks on the MNIST and Fashion-MNIST datasets. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a key area of research in AI. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the proposed technique could potentially be applied to network compression, which is a relevant topic in social and information networks.
